{
  "text": "Our results also revealed the putative loss or formation of a pseudogene of the infA gene in E. macrophylla (Fig 2B) . Moreover, the loss of the infA gene of 12 rosids was observed in this study (Fig 4) . Su et al. [CITATION_1] showed that Quercus, Francoa and Cucumis contain intact infA genes; however, no infA gene was observed in Cucumis in the present study (Fig 4) .",
